1
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:06,373
<i>I compared the procurement list Tsuda had</i>

2
00:00:06,439 --> 00:00:09,075
with the subsidiary ledger
from the Karashima Metal Factory.

3
00:00:09,142 --> 00:00:12,245
In Tsuda's procurement list,
there was SNCM.

4
00:00:12,312 --> 00:00:14,114
This metal is used for…

5
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:15,548
handguns.

6
00:00:15,615 --> 00:00:18,018
<i>That gun might not</i>
<i>have been meant for use,</i>

7
00:00:18,084 --> 00:00:19,919
<i>but rather something</i>
<i>manufactured at the factory.</i>

8
00:00:19,986 --> 00:00:23,356
<i>Tsuda was probably investigating</i>
<i>the gun smugglers.</i>

9
00:00:23,423 --> 00:00:25,725
<i>If some kind of incident happened then…</i>

10
00:00:25,792 --> 00:00:27,961
The ones who killed our parents

11
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:30,163
might be the Igarashi-gumi.

12
00:00:45,178 --> 00:00:46,212
He's a weirdo.

13
00:00:46,279 --> 00:00:47,147
Let's go.

14
00:01:16,176 --> 00:01:18,178
-I’ll leave the rest to you.
-Yes.

15
00:01:25,585 --> 00:01:27,387
How did you know he was a thief?

16
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:29,422
Just a coincidence.

17
00:01:30,190 --> 00:01:33,560
You happened to be looking at him,
and he happened to commit the crime?

18
00:01:34,627 --> 00:01:35,662
What is it?

19
00:01:36,796 --> 00:01:39,599
If you got serious,
you might just be a decent detective.

20
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:43,436
If I had lived properly,
I wouldn't even be a detective.

21
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:49,843
Then what would you be doing?

22
00:01:50,477 --> 00:01:52,912
Who knows?
I've never even thought about it.

23
00:01:52,979 --> 00:01:55,381
You would probably
be getting a divorce by now.

24
00:01:55,448 --> 00:01:57,817
At least let me get married first.

25
00:01:59,052 --> 00:02:02,088
Haruko investigated Tsuda’s room
the other day, right?

26
00:02:03,756 --> 00:02:04,924
Three…

27
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:21,174
This is terrible.

28
00:02:31,918 --> 00:02:34,187
Haruko already checked this place?

29
00:02:34,854 --> 00:02:36,022
Should we lift the futon?

30
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:39,359
Anyway, what was the motive
of the guys who attacked him?

31
00:02:41,961 --> 00:02:42,662
Hey.

32
00:02:43,796 --> 00:02:44,731
Oh, hey.

33
00:02:44,797 --> 00:02:46,299
Wrong room.

34
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:51,171
The ones who trashed Tsuda’s room
were members of the Igarashi-gumi.

35
00:02:51,237 --> 00:02:52,739
The Igarashi-gumi?

36
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:56,976
The guy who stole Tsuda’s backpack
told me after I bought him a beer.

37
00:02:57,043 --> 00:02:58,411
Hey, where is it?

38
00:02:58,478 --> 00:02:59,779
Hold it right there!

39
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:01,114
Hey, Tsuda, you bastard!

40
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:02,715
Come back!

41
00:03:02,782 --> 00:03:03,816
Hey!

42
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:11,491
The heck? There's nothing here,
just books…

43
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:16,062
<i>On the back of the Karashima</i>
<i>Metal Factory photo,</i>

44
00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:17,897
<i>it said "tools."</i>

45
00:03:18,898 --> 00:03:21,834
<i>It seems those guys took</i>
<i>all the notebooks and files.</i>

46
00:03:22,535 --> 00:03:24,771
"Tools" is slang for handguns.

47
00:03:25,338 --> 00:03:28,374
No doubt, that factory
is connected to the Igarashi-gumi.

48
00:03:29,108 --> 00:03:32,478
Then what they took
was Tsuda’s research notebook.

49
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:33,913
That notebook

50
00:03:34,981 --> 00:03:37,517
might contain clues from 30 years ago.

51
00:03:38,985 --> 00:03:42,689
Problem now is… how do we
get close to the Igarashi-gumi?

52
00:03:44,324 --> 00:03:46,159
CHINESE RESTAURANT
MOCCHAN

53
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:51,064
Welcome. Oh, hey.

54
00:03:51,130 --> 00:03:52,031
Well…

55
00:03:52,098 --> 00:03:53,399
Hello.

56
00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:55,602
-Oh, hello.
-Please check this.

57
00:03:55,668 --> 00:03:57,237
We have to hurry.

58
00:03:57,303 --> 00:04:00,640
We need to get that notebook
before the gang members dispose of it.

59
00:04:01,507 --> 00:04:03,176
What happened back then?

60
00:04:03,977 --> 00:04:06,512
If we find out what went on
at the factory, I'm sure…

61
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:09,048
Sure of what?

62
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:16,155
What are you two
investigating about the factory?

63
00:04:16,723 --> 00:04:17,991
Fumi.

64
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:20,960
Makoto,

65
00:04:21,628 --> 00:04:22,662
it's nice to see you.

66
00:04:24,831 --> 00:04:26,399
Minoru.

67
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:28,968
I heard you're with
the Kanagawa Prefectural Police?

68
00:04:29,035 --> 00:04:30,203
What?

69
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:33,273
It seems you visited our tax accountant

70
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,209
and looked at the factory ledger.

71
00:04:38,311 --> 00:04:41,681
Sneaking around isn't a good thing.

72
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:43,716
I'm sorry.

73
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:46,052
I just wanted to know
about the metal used for the robot.

74
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:47,487
Is that really all?

75
00:04:48,921 --> 00:04:50,657
Yes, just that.

76
00:04:51,891 --> 00:04:52,759
What about you?

77
00:04:54,594 --> 00:04:55,628
Me?

78
00:04:56,262 --> 00:04:58,464
Is there anything you’re hiding from us?

79
00:05:03,703 --> 00:05:04,604
What do you think?

80
00:05:04,671 --> 00:05:06,506
I’m the one asking.

81
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,310
-What happened at that factory…
-Mogi!

82
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:12,845
-Thanks for the meal.
-Oh, sure.

83
00:05:12,912 --> 00:05:13,746
Fumi!

84
00:05:16,382 --> 00:05:18,184
I'm glad I saw you.

85
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,520
Mogi.

86
00:05:20,586 --> 00:05:22,121
You can keep the change.

87
00:05:23,022 --> 00:05:24,490
You're too kind.

88
00:05:24,557 --> 00:05:25,925
Thank you very much.

89
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,636
Was this really for the best?

90
00:05:37,303 --> 00:05:38,237
Mr. Uno.

91
00:05:38,304 --> 00:05:39,172
THE EMPTY GARDEN

92
00:05:39,238 --> 00:05:40,940
Please remember…

93
00:05:42,308 --> 00:05:43,876
what happened that day.

94
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:47,947
Doctor.

95
00:05:50,149 --> 00:05:51,818
Now, you're quits.

96
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:53,986
You're even.

97
00:06:00,493 --> 00:06:02,562
Nice and even.

98
00:06:03,763 --> 00:06:05,131
Nice and even.

99
00:06:07,934 --> 00:06:08,835
Nice…

100
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:17,910
The deceased is
Ayaka Nishiura, 29 years old.

101
00:06:17,977 --> 00:06:22,148
She was in a vehicle accident, brought
to the hospital, and pronounced dead.

102
00:06:22,648 --> 00:06:23,983
Examiner Tagusari.

103
00:06:24,851 --> 00:06:28,121
<i>As the victim's fingernails</i>
<i>were bright red, we performed an autopsy.</i>

104
00:06:28,187 --> 00:06:32,658
The results showed the cause of death
was not injuries from the collision,

105
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:34,494
but carbon monoxide poisoning.

106
00:06:36,662 --> 00:06:38,164
What does that mean?

107
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:39,799
Carbon monoxide…

108
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:42,435
But the car wasn't on fire, right?

109
00:06:42,502 --> 00:06:45,605
We believe she inhaled it
before the accident, while driving.

110
00:06:46,506 --> 00:06:48,174
While driving?

111
00:06:48,941 --> 00:06:52,378
After the autopsy, the coroner requested
an investigation of the vehicle.

112
00:06:52,445 --> 00:06:53,713
As a result,

113
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:56,349
it was found that the flange
connecting the muffler

114
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,785
and the exhaust tailpipe
was unnaturally loose.

115
00:06:58,851 --> 00:06:59,719
The flange?

116
00:06:59,786 --> 00:07:01,354
This part right here.

117
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,722
NISHIURA
FLANGE / ENGINE

118
00:07:02,789 --> 00:07:05,525
While the car was stopped
at a red light, exhaust gas entered

119
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:07,360
through a crack in the car's lower part.

120
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:08,928
That is all.

121
00:07:11,364 --> 00:07:13,800
Then she had carbon monoxide poisoning.

122
00:07:13,866 --> 00:07:15,234
In other words,

123
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:17,270
it was murder?

124
00:07:27,313 --> 00:07:28,748
Thanks for your cooperation.

125
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:30,416
-It’s on the fourth floor. Follow me.
-Yes.

126
00:07:31,517 --> 00:07:33,186
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

127
00:07:33,252 --> 00:07:34,754
Excuse me.

128
00:07:44,997 --> 00:07:47,266
This is Ayaka Nishiura’s residence, right?

129
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:50,503
Yes.

130
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:51,704
Who are you?

131
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:54,440
I'm Kudo from the Aoi Station.

132
00:07:54,507 --> 00:07:57,443
Pardon me, but what was
your relationship with Ms. Nishiura?

133
00:07:58,010 --> 00:08:00,913
I was dating Ayaka. My name is Agatsuma.

134
00:08:03,249 --> 00:08:04,817
Why are the police here?

135
00:08:05,685 --> 00:08:07,854
There’s something
that caught our attention.

136
00:08:09,088 --> 00:08:11,057
Ayaka's death was an accident, wasn't it?

137
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:15,862
Has she been acting strangely lately?

138
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:21,767
She changed.

139
00:08:22,368 --> 00:08:24,670
Quite a lot compared to back then.

140
00:08:28,941 --> 00:08:30,343
Three years ago,

141
00:08:31,577 --> 00:08:35,648
Ayaka accidentally
killed someone in a car crash.

142
00:08:36,582 --> 00:08:38,784
It's so warm! Thank you!

143
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:49,962
<i>Ayaka didn't commit any violation.</i>

144
00:08:51,597 --> 00:08:53,766
She was just driving normally.

145
00:08:56,802 --> 00:08:58,604
If that person hadn't jumped out,

146
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:02,041
she never would have caused the accident.

147
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:06,712
It was one week before our wedding.

148
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:10,349
Though it was unintentional,

149
00:09:11,183 --> 00:09:14,220
she was depressed
about having killed someone.

150
00:09:15,087 --> 00:09:16,589
She couldn't work,

151
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:19,592
get married, or do anything.

152
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:26,065
But over time,
she was moving forward little by little.

153
00:09:31,437 --> 00:09:33,940
I had just proposed for the second time.

154
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:36,709
I'm sorry.

155
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,921
It’s just… unbearable, isn't it?

156
00:09:52,858 --> 00:09:54,927
A second proposal, huh?

157
00:09:57,029 --> 00:10:00,900
The dead do not get a second chance.

158
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:09,308
Ayaka Nishiura, who died yesterday,
caused an accident three years ago

159
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:11,677
that resulted in the death
of Ms. Yoko Uno.

160
00:10:11,744 --> 00:10:15,414
At the time, Ms. Nishiura was not found
negligent and not prosecuted.

161
00:10:16,048 --> 00:10:18,084
But it seems Yoko’s husband,

162
00:10:18,985 --> 00:10:20,286
Takamichi Uno,

163
00:10:20,353 --> 00:10:23,856
repeatedly protested to the police
and prosecutors about that result.

164
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:26,626
Do you think the husband killed her?

165
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,694
Did you find something?

166
00:10:29,195 --> 00:10:30,029
Hey.

167
00:10:30,096 --> 00:10:30,930
Yes.

168
00:10:32,098 --> 00:10:36,402
Early in the morning of the day
Ayaka Nishiura died, a person was seen

169
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:39,672
crawling under her car
in the apartment's parking lot.

170
00:10:40,606 --> 00:10:42,408
Looks like Uno.

171
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:46,312
Furthermore, Uno is a mechanic
at an automobile factory.

172
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:48,848
That’s why he was able
to tamper with the flange.

173
00:10:48,914 --> 00:10:50,583
Guess this case is open-and-shut.

174
00:10:51,117 --> 00:10:54,654
I’ll question Uno tomorrow,
so I have to report to the superiors.

175
00:10:56,422 --> 00:10:59,091
But it was an unavoidable
accident, wasn't it?

176
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:01,093
She suddenly jumped onto the road.

177
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:04,163
It’s just something
that could happen to anyone.

178
00:11:05,064 --> 00:11:08,200
Uno did it as revenge
for his wife's death.

179
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:15,675
Would you really seek revenge for that?

180
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:20,413
And three years have passed already.

181
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:23,382
Maybe he tried to forgive, but couldn't.

182
00:11:23,449 --> 00:11:26,285
For someone with a grudge,
his method was too roundabout.

183
00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:28,988
If you hate someone,
you would confront them.

184
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:31,691
Are you saying Uno isn't the culprit?

185
00:11:35,561 --> 00:11:36,629
Who knows?

186
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:45,705
He asked me about the shootings
in Yomogida Town 30 years ago.

187
00:11:45,771 --> 00:11:47,473
From 30 years ago?

188
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:51,410
He said a colleague
at Totsuka North was pursuing it,

189
00:11:51,477 --> 00:11:55,047
but apparently, Totsuka North
isn't handling any such case.

190
00:11:55,614 --> 00:11:58,417
Do you know
what Tagusari is investigating?

191
00:12:22,108 --> 00:12:23,142
You're Ms. Fumi…

192
00:12:24,143 --> 00:12:25,678
Karashima, right?

193
00:12:26,979 --> 00:12:28,247
Who are you?

194
00:12:30,382 --> 00:12:31,517
This…

195
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:32,985
Can you buy this off me?

196
00:12:34,286 --> 00:12:37,523
Everything about
what happened 30 years ago

197
00:12:38,057 --> 00:12:39,391
is written here.

198
00:12:45,831 --> 00:12:48,934
ASAI AUTOMOBILE INC.

199
00:12:53,305 --> 00:12:54,974
I'm from the Aoi Station.

200
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:57,143
You're Takamichi Uno, correct?

201
00:12:59,378 --> 00:13:00,212
Yes.

202
00:13:00,846 --> 00:13:05,584
Where were you two days ago,
May 13th, around 4:00 a.m.?

203
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:10,489
-I was sleeping at home.
-Is there anyone who can vouch for that?

204
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:12,925
No one.

205
00:13:13,893 --> 00:13:16,362
My wife passed away,
and I don't have children.

206
00:13:17,863 --> 00:13:20,900
You know Ayaka Nishiura, don't you?

207
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:30,476
Mr. Uno?

208
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:35,314
There’s no way I could forget.

209
00:13:35,948 --> 00:13:37,650
What about Ms. Nishiura’s accident?

210
00:13:38,784 --> 00:13:40,019
I saw it on the news.

211
00:13:40,085 --> 00:13:42,788
Could you come to the station
to give a detailed account?

212
00:13:43,455 --> 00:13:44,924
I have plans today.

213
00:14:13,485 --> 00:14:15,020
The city office?

214
00:14:21,994 --> 00:14:23,062
Thank you so much.

215
00:14:23,128 --> 00:14:24,263
Yes, come back anytime.

216
00:14:24,330 --> 00:14:27,333
You might think you're not
doing great as a mom, but you are!

217
00:14:27,399 --> 00:14:29,268
So cheer up, okay?

218
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:34,740
Bye-bye!

219
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:38,277
Thank you for waiting.

220
00:14:38,344 --> 00:14:39,812
Shall we go inside?

221
00:14:46,652 --> 00:14:49,054
WELFARE OFFICE
CONSULTING ROOM

222
00:14:49,121 --> 00:14:50,656
It seems Mr. Uno has been using

223
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:53,158
the consultation service here
for three years.

224
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:54,994
So after the accident?

225
00:14:55,661 --> 00:14:58,764
He started coming for advice
after losing his wife.

226
00:15:02,534 --> 00:15:04,370
Seems that way.

227
00:15:08,173 --> 00:15:11,810
Just having someone listen to you
gives a sense of relief.

228
00:15:14,146 --> 00:15:17,316
Staff here visited my home too.

229
00:15:18,217 --> 00:15:19,985
My mother was so annoyed, though.

230
00:15:25,057 --> 00:15:26,558
What about your home?

231
00:15:28,928 --> 00:15:31,163
What kind of person is your mother?

232
00:15:39,305 --> 00:15:41,040
Couldn't hide anything from her.

233
00:15:43,475 --> 00:15:44,643
If I lied

234
00:15:45,511 --> 00:15:47,446
or hid something, she would find out.

235
00:15:49,548 --> 00:15:51,684
She might have bugged us.

236
00:15:56,855 --> 00:15:58,123
That’s nice.

237
00:15:59,024 --> 00:16:00,392
What’s nice about it?

238
00:16:02,828 --> 00:16:03,662
It just…

239
00:16:04,263 --> 00:16:06,432
feels like a real family.

240
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:17,376
Please contact me
whenever you feel like it.

241
00:16:17,443 --> 00:16:18,711
Thank you very much.

242
00:16:19,912 --> 00:16:21,180
The subject is leaving.

243
00:16:24,049 --> 00:16:26,952
Sorry to bother you at work.
I'm Kudo from the Aoi Station.

244
00:16:27,019 --> 00:16:27,853
Oh, hello.

245
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:28,754
I'm Tagusari.

246
00:16:30,689 --> 00:16:31,690
Mr. Tagusari?

247
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:36,962
Oh, it's nothing. Oh, my.

248
00:16:37,029 --> 00:16:38,998
I just thought, it's such a rare name.

249
00:16:39,932 --> 00:16:40,766
Oh, right.

250
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:43,702
I’m from the Welfare
and Health Department.

251
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:45,104
The name is Hatano.

252
00:16:47,406 --> 00:16:48,374
Thank you.

253
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,274
WELFARE CONSULTANT

254
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,809
Please have a seat.

255
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:53,812
I’ll make some tea now.

256
00:16:57,649 --> 00:17:00,586
We want to ask about Mr. Uno,
whom you are counseling.

257
00:17:00,652 --> 00:17:03,655
What kind of things
does he consult with you about?

258
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:10,596
Have you ever heard
the name Ayaka Nishiura?

259
00:17:13,298 --> 00:17:14,933
I’m sorry, but…

260
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:16,635
I cannot answer that.

261
00:17:19,071 --> 00:17:22,741
Our relationship with consultees
is built on trust.

262
00:17:23,475 --> 00:17:26,145
I can't disclose information
without their consent.

263
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:28,847
There’s a possibility it’s related
to a criminal case.

264
00:17:28,914 --> 00:17:31,050
Please, you must understand.

265
00:17:33,819 --> 00:17:35,087
Here.

266
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:41,326
Were you able to solve his problems?

267
00:17:44,263 --> 00:17:45,998
The reasons Mr. Uno came here.

268
00:17:49,468 --> 00:17:51,403
"What can talking even change?"

269
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,205
Is that what you think?

270
00:18:03,515 --> 00:18:04,616
But…

271
00:18:04,683 --> 00:18:07,653
isn't it painful to keep it
all bottled up inside?

272
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:13,659
"No one understands anyway."

273
00:18:15,561 --> 00:18:17,863
"That's why I don't trust anyone."

274
00:18:19,531 --> 00:18:23,635
If you keep listening
only to your own voice like that,

275
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:29,675
eventually you lose sight
of what's at your core.

276
00:18:32,244 --> 00:18:34,613
You come to hate what you love,

277
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:37,850
or pretend to be fine when you're scared…

278
00:18:40,752 --> 00:18:41,820
For example,

279
00:18:42,888 --> 00:18:44,323
even to those close to you.

280
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:52,798
I'm here to help nurture
that core so it can bloom.

281
00:18:54,066 --> 00:18:57,002
I will cooperate with you,
but there are things I can't do.

282
00:18:59,338 --> 00:19:01,540
Didn't that give you the chills?

283
00:19:01,607 --> 00:19:04,209
It's like she saw right through us.

284
00:19:32,771 --> 00:19:34,640
<i>The one I'm stuck on is the mother.</i>

285
00:19:34,706 --> 00:19:35,707
TELESEEK
ONE NEW MESSAGE

286
00:19:35,774 --> 00:19:38,243
<i>I saw a TeleSeek notification</i>
<i>on her phone.</i>

287
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:40,879
<i>That app that doesn't store</i>
<i>message history?</i>

288
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:51,790
Thank you. It's a real help.

289
00:19:56,728 --> 00:20:00,799
MAKOTO TAGUSARI
LOOK INTO THIS WELFARE WORKER FOR ME

290
00:20:04,336 --> 00:20:07,940
-Why don't you get something to read?
-There’s nothing I want to read.

291
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:11,410
Is that Igarashi-gumi guy really coming?

292
00:20:17,749 --> 00:20:18,617
Did you see?

293
00:20:19,818 --> 00:20:20,886
See what?

294
00:20:21,620 --> 00:20:23,188
So that’s your type.

295
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:26,325
I wasn't even looking.

296
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,760
How many years has it been?

297
00:20:29,261 --> 00:20:30,963
You should get a girlfriend soon.

298
00:20:31,029 --> 00:20:34,066
-Shut up, leave me alone.
-You liked her, didn't you?

299
00:20:34,132 --> 00:20:36,702
I've known you since you were this big.

300
00:20:40,872 --> 00:20:41,840
Haruko.

301
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:42,741
Yes.

302
00:20:46,545 --> 00:20:47,813
0.7, right?

303
00:20:47,879 --> 00:20:48,814
Yes.

304
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:53,151
-It's your first buy, so I put in extra.
-Thanks.

305
00:20:57,122 --> 00:20:59,858
Guess there's no point
in arresting a low-level grunt.

306
00:21:03,328 --> 00:21:05,097
But, the Igarashi-gumi

307
00:21:05,163 --> 00:21:08,834
making college students push drugs?
Times sure have changed.

308
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:11,370
These days, they prefer disposable labor.

309
00:21:15,674 --> 00:21:19,611
However, that also makes
the loose ends easier to find.

310
00:21:25,651 --> 00:21:28,120
If you hate it that much,
why don't you quit?

311
00:21:29,688 --> 00:21:32,858
Quit selling stuff like that,
and just work a normal job.

312
00:21:35,994 --> 00:21:38,630
You’re still young, after all.

313
00:21:38,697 --> 00:21:40,632
Yoshiyuki Nakajima.

314
00:21:41,566 --> 00:21:42,968
How do you know my name?

315
00:21:43,835 --> 00:21:45,971
We already have your gang's information.

316
00:21:47,205 --> 00:21:48,774
You really want to quit, right?

317
00:21:50,509 --> 00:21:52,577
But if I quit, I'll get killed.

318
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,082
Shall I help you escape?

319
00:21:58,216 --> 00:22:01,386
In exchange,
tell me the day the drugs are delivered

320
00:22:01,453 --> 00:22:04,089
to your Igarashi-gumi boss.

321
00:22:10,395 --> 00:22:12,164
What are you doing here?

322
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:18,904
Fumi is at work, so I came in her stead.

323
00:22:20,072 --> 00:22:21,039
But…

324
00:22:21,106 --> 00:22:24,142
I just got a message
saying her work is done.

325
00:22:24,810 --> 00:22:25,911
I see.

326
00:22:25,977 --> 00:22:26,878
Yes.

327
00:22:28,580 --> 00:22:30,882
Oh, welcome back.

328
00:22:30,949 --> 00:22:31,817
You're home?

329
00:22:31,883 --> 00:22:34,219
Yes, I came back just now.

330
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:37,823
Mogi, thanks!

331
00:22:37,889 --> 00:22:38,990
-It was nothing.
-Yes!

332
00:22:39,057 --> 00:22:41,293
Thanks to you, I got some great photos.

333
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:42,627
I’m glad.

334
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:46,198
I heard… it was an important job?

335
00:22:46,264 --> 00:22:48,567
Yes, an advertisement.

336
00:22:48,633 --> 00:22:50,702
It's a huge job.

337
00:22:50,769 --> 00:22:52,237
Yukiteru?

338
00:22:53,405 --> 00:22:57,209
Since I'm here,
I thought I would go home with you, Mom.

339
00:22:57,275 --> 00:22:59,878
Karu, that's enough for today.

340
00:22:59,945 --> 00:23:02,547
I'll quickly clean the bathtub.

341
00:23:03,648 --> 00:23:05,217
The coffee is ready.

342
00:23:05,283 --> 00:23:06,685
Thank you.

343
00:23:08,487 --> 00:23:11,957
Mogi. Stay and have some coffee
until Karu is done.

344
00:23:12,457 --> 00:23:14,192
-Okay?
-Thank you.

345
00:23:15,861 --> 00:23:17,028
Mogi.

346
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:19,097
Did you hear anything?

347
00:23:19,998 --> 00:23:22,901
No, I didn't talk to the doctor…

348
00:23:22,968 --> 00:23:25,570
Not that, I meant those brothers.

349
00:23:27,773 --> 00:23:29,474
Makoto and Minoru?

350
00:23:30,275 --> 00:23:34,146
Is the notebook they were talking
about the one that Tsuda had?

351
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:38,250
No, I don't know anything.

352
00:23:38,316 --> 00:23:39,918
How troublesome.

353
00:23:40,952 --> 00:23:44,089
If strange rumors start,
it will affect my work.

354
00:24:02,474 --> 00:24:03,708
Oh, right.

355
00:24:04,843 --> 00:24:06,178
Take this with you.

356
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:09,247
Karu likes sweets, doesn't she?

357
00:24:10,048 --> 00:24:10,882
Here.

358
00:24:16,588 --> 00:24:17,422
Are you okay?

359
00:24:17,956 --> 00:24:18,857
All right?

360
00:24:25,263 --> 00:24:26,231
What's wrong?

361
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,335
It's nothing.

362
00:24:31,069 --> 00:24:32,871
You got a class reunion invite.

363
00:24:34,973 --> 00:24:36,274
Throw it away.

364
00:24:36,775 --> 00:24:37,642
Are you sure?

365
00:24:38,243 --> 00:24:39,678
I have nothing to say to them.

366
00:24:46,184 --> 00:24:49,621
It's all complaints about wives
and worries about raising kids.

367
00:24:49,688 --> 00:24:51,122
Those are the only topics.

368
00:24:51,957 --> 00:24:55,594
And once they get drunk,
someone will start talking about that day.

369
00:24:57,062 --> 00:24:58,897
"Tagusari worked hard."

370
00:24:59,731 --> 00:25:02,167
"Tagusari did well getting past it."

371
00:25:04,002 --> 00:25:05,737
"We're friends for life."

372
00:25:07,205 --> 00:25:10,075
Even though they forgot all about
what happened until they saw us.

373
00:25:10,642 --> 00:25:13,478
I can't stand being the subject
of gossip for their drinking sessions.

374
00:25:16,248 --> 00:25:17,382
Compared to that…

375
00:25:18,850 --> 00:25:21,086
it’s much better to drink alone.

376
00:25:27,659 --> 00:25:29,694
I'm hungry. Is there anything to eat?

377
00:25:30,495 --> 00:25:33,598
-I can make some <i>chukadon</i>.
-Extra quail eggs, please.

378
00:25:33,665 --> 00:25:34,699
Got it.

379
00:25:42,307 --> 00:25:44,876
When will you catch them?

380
00:25:44,943 --> 00:25:47,913
Why did my mom and dad die?

381
00:25:49,347 --> 00:25:52,284
<i>Isn't it painful to keep it</i>
<i>all bottled up inside?</i>

382
00:25:58,690 --> 00:25:59,658
What's wrong?

383
00:26:00,158 --> 00:26:02,227
I can't break Uno's alibi.

384
00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:05,897
The security cameras
around his house turned up nothing.

385
00:26:06,765 --> 00:26:08,233
What about you, Ms. Kudo?

386
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:11,269
Because of confidentiality,
the city office won't say anything.

387
00:26:11,336 --> 00:26:12,437
Why?

388
00:26:12,504 --> 00:26:13,805
The evidence is all there.

389
00:26:13,872 --> 00:26:15,507
Let's talk over here.

390
00:26:16,007 --> 00:26:18,109
That man killed my father.

391
00:26:18,743 --> 00:26:20,011
-Why?
-What's happened?

392
00:26:22,247 --> 00:26:23,148
This.

393
00:26:23,214 --> 00:26:25,383
I KILLED MY COWORKER 32 YEARS AGO
A CONFESSION 17 YEARS AFTER THE STATUTE

394
00:26:25,450 --> 00:26:27,552
An unsolved disappearance case.

395
00:26:28,153 --> 00:26:32,023
The culprit buried the body
under the boards in his garden,

396
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:34,726
but it was being dug up
for land readjustment.

397
00:26:34,793 --> 00:26:36,828
Seems he turned himself in yesterday.

398
00:26:36,895 --> 00:26:39,564
But the case's statute of limitations
expired in 2009.

399
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:41,733
You know who the culprit is.

400
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:44,402
Arrest him! Please!

401
00:26:44,469 --> 00:26:46,237
-Please.
-Ishizaka.

402
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:50,342
Okay.

403
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:55,814
If only the case had been one year later.

404
00:26:56,414 --> 00:26:59,084
No more statute of limitations
for murders after 2009…

405
00:26:59,150 --> 00:27:00,151
Hello.

406
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:03,755
Don't tell Tagusari.

407
00:27:03,822 --> 00:27:04,856
Why?

408
00:27:06,024 --> 00:27:08,226
Come on, just go with him.

409
00:27:20,338 --> 00:27:23,608
First Division will re-examine
Uno’s background and relationships.

410
00:27:24,142 --> 00:27:27,912
Aoi Station investigators, expand the
search area from Ms. Nishiura’s home

411
00:27:27,979 --> 00:27:29,347
and check security cameras.

412
00:27:29,414 --> 00:27:30,415
Yes, sir!

413
00:27:34,019 --> 00:27:36,655
If we can confirm Uno’s face
on a security camera…

414
00:27:36,721 --> 00:27:38,289
I won't let him get away.

415
00:27:38,356 --> 00:27:39,958
I'll crush his alibi.

416
00:27:46,264 --> 00:27:47,499
Excuse me.

417
00:27:47,565 --> 00:27:49,601
I'm from the Aoi Station.

418
00:27:50,869 --> 00:27:53,538
Could we check your CCTV footage?

419
00:27:53,605 --> 00:27:55,173
It's right here.

420
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,207
Thank you.

421
00:27:56,274 --> 00:27:58,777
-Please let me know when you're finished.
-We will.

422
00:28:00,845 --> 00:28:03,181
I'll fast-forward to May 13th.

423
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:11,356
I'll be right back.

424
00:28:13,658 --> 00:28:14,959
Yes, this is Kudo.

425
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:22,400
Are you working?

426
00:28:26,738 --> 00:28:27,806
Why are you here?

427
00:28:27,872 --> 00:28:30,241
I just had some business around here.

428
00:28:30,809 --> 00:28:31,810
Business?

429
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:36,314
Didn't you use to live in Yomogida?

430
00:28:39,751 --> 00:28:40,785
How do you know that?

431
00:28:41,653 --> 00:28:42,821
So I was right.

432
00:28:42,887 --> 00:28:47,459
I thought I had heard the name
Tagusari somewhere before,

433
00:28:47,525 --> 00:28:49,461
so I searched for it online.

434
00:28:51,296 --> 00:28:52,664
I see.

435
00:28:53,698 --> 00:28:55,467
So you became a detective.

436
00:28:57,035 --> 00:28:58,903
Is it out of a sense of justice?

437
00:28:59,938 --> 00:29:03,675
Or is there some other reason?

438
00:29:08,713 --> 00:29:10,515
Don't worry about me.

439
00:29:18,156 --> 00:29:21,760
Mr. Uno lost his dear wife in an accident.

440
00:29:23,361 --> 00:29:28,633
But the driver, Ms. Nishiura,
insisted it was his wife’s fault

441
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:31,436
and refused to admit
her own mistake until the very end.

442
00:29:33,271 --> 00:29:34,873
Even though she killed someone,

443
00:29:35,573 --> 00:29:38,476
she wasn't held accountable for the crime.

444
00:29:40,478 --> 00:29:43,915
After that, Ms. Nishiura,
supported by her boyfriend,

445
00:29:43,982 --> 00:29:47,585
began returning to society, and started

446
00:29:49,654 --> 00:29:51,122
driving a car again.

447
00:29:56,094 --> 00:29:58,029
Everything goes back to normal.

448
00:29:59,531 --> 00:30:01,966
Except for Mr. Uno’s wife, who was gone.

449
00:30:08,006 --> 00:30:10,241
You know the pain
of the forgotten bereaved,

450
00:30:11,609 --> 00:30:13,011
don't you?

451
00:30:25,023 --> 00:30:27,959
Why don't you stop carrying
the burden all by yourself?

452
00:30:29,294 --> 00:30:33,031
Please, tell me what's at your core.

453
00:30:35,066 --> 00:30:36,701
Today, at 6:00 p.m.

454
00:30:36,768 --> 00:30:38,870
I'll be waiting for you
at the city office.

455
00:30:47,779 --> 00:30:50,882
Hey, check your phone!

456
00:30:50,949 --> 00:30:52,417
Haruko called me.

457
00:30:52,483 --> 00:30:54,519
She said she couldn't get through to you.

458
00:30:55,353 --> 00:30:56,321
I see.

459
00:30:56,821 --> 00:30:59,424
You're investigating Ms. Hatano
from the city office?

460
00:31:01,025 --> 00:31:02,627
I was just a little curious.

461
00:31:03,828 --> 00:31:05,396
How was the CCTV footage?

462
00:31:10,768 --> 00:31:12,637
Nothing was caught on camera.

463
00:31:13,338 --> 00:31:14,639
I see.

464
00:31:15,807 --> 00:31:18,209
-Haruko is asking to meet.
-I'll leave it to you.

465
00:31:34,659 --> 00:31:35,894
Where's Makoto?

466
00:31:36,961 --> 00:31:39,264
It seems he has
some business to attend to.

467
00:31:41,432 --> 00:31:44,936
The other day, Mr. Tagusari and I
were talking about family.

468
00:31:45,503 --> 00:31:47,405
What about you, Haruko?

469
00:31:48,139 --> 00:31:49,474
What?

470
00:31:49,540 --> 00:31:51,075
Do you see your family?

471
00:31:54,979 --> 00:31:56,247
I do.

472
00:31:57,048 --> 00:31:58,716
I see my father here.

473
00:32:01,085 --> 00:32:03,254
It was so long ago,

474
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:06,658
he got drunk and fell into the sea.

475
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:12,597
My mom and brother died in an accident
when I was in grade school.

476
00:32:16,100 --> 00:32:19,637
I couldn't say goodbye or thank you.

477
00:32:22,907 --> 00:32:26,477
So, it might be better
to see your mother while you still can.

478
00:32:31,783 --> 00:32:32,650
Okay.

479
00:32:34,986 --> 00:32:37,689
From that reply,
I'm sure you won't see her.

480
00:32:41,159 --> 00:32:42,794
You're sharp, Haruko.

481
00:32:44,896 --> 00:32:46,397
Oh, right.

482
00:32:47,165 --> 00:32:48,733
Before I forget.

483
00:32:51,135 --> 00:32:52,837
Oh, it’s about Ms. Hatano, right?

484
00:32:52,904 --> 00:32:53,972
Right.

485
00:32:54,472 --> 00:32:58,409
No matter where I dug,
I only heard good rumors about her.

486
00:32:59,243 --> 00:33:00,411
I knew it.

487
00:33:01,012 --> 00:33:03,881
I wonder why Mr. Tagusari
made you look into her?

488
00:33:05,149 --> 00:33:08,119
Are the drugs being delivered today?

489
00:33:08,186 --> 00:33:12,123
Based on the college student's testimony,
we're going to raid the Igarashi-gumi now.

490
00:33:12,757 --> 00:33:15,893
I'm sure they have other offenses,
so go and do a thorough sweep.

491
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,161
I know.

492
00:33:21,132 --> 00:33:23,167
I heard all about it.

493
00:33:23,234 --> 00:33:24,769
You caught onto something big!

494
00:33:24,836 --> 00:33:27,705
I handed it over
to the Organized Crime Department.

495
00:33:27,772 --> 00:33:30,241
What? What a waste.

496
00:33:30,308 --> 00:33:32,610
They said they'll pay back
the favor someday.

497
00:33:33,544 --> 00:33:37,648
Still, you did great
finding out the delivery date.

498
00:33:37,715 --> 00:33:39,250
It was just a coincidence.

499
00:33:40,351 --> 00:33:44,255
MAKOTO - WE'RE SWEEPING THE IGARASHI-GUMI
I'M SURE WE'LL FIND TSUDA'S NOTEBOOK

500
00:33:52,063 --> 00:33:55,333
<i>Today at 6:00 p.m. I'll be waiting</i>
<i>for you at the city office.</i>

501
00:34:04,542 --> 00:34:07,745
The users of the Welfare and Health
Department that Uno visited.

502
00:34:07,812 --> 00:34:10,248
You did well to get this.

503
00:34:10,314 --> 00:34:12,383
The city office's security must be tight.

504
00:34:12,450 --> 00:34:15,219
It's thanks to an informant
Mr. Tagusari uses.

505
00:34:15,286 --> 00:34:16,454
Tagusari?

506
00:34:16,521 --> 00:34:18,956
She's a former newspaper reporter,
very capable.

507
00:34:20,925 --> 00:34:21,759
Ms. Kudo.

508
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:25,630
-Is anything wrong with the users here?
-Here.

509
00:34:25,696 --> 00:34:26,697
ATSUKO NARITA

510
00:34:26,764 --> 00:34:28,132
Atsuko Narita?

511
00:34:28,633 --> 00:34:30,735
The mother from the entrance exam case?

512
00:34:31,302 --> 00:34:35,273
Ms. Hatano, the consultant,
was in charge of both Uno and Narita.

513
00:34:35,339 --> 00:34:39,310
Doesn't it bother you that she's
consulting with two of our suspects?

514
00:34:39,377 --> 00:34:41,279
Sayoko Hatano…

515
00:34:41,345 --> 00:34:45,550
However, she has a good reputation
among other staff and users.

516
00:34:45,616 --> 00:34:48,619
Uno purchased an old vehicle
that was about to be scrapped.

517
00:34:48,686 --> 00:34:49,854
About to be scrapped?

518
00:34:49,921 --> 00:34:51,055
Why would he buy it?

519
00:34:51,122 --> 00:34:54,625
Around the same time, he also got
an exhaust gas meter from the shop.

520
00:34:54,692 --> 00:34:56,694
Was he experimenting with exhaust leaks?

521
00:34:56,761 --> 00:34:58,162
Bring him in for voluntary questioning.

522
00:34:58,229 --> 00:34:59,430
Yes, sir!

523
00:35:20,618 --> 00:35:23,154
MINORU

524
00:35:29,927 --> 00:35:32,063
I knew you would come.

525
00:35:33,498 --> 00:35:34,732
Makoto Tagusari.

526
00:35:39,670 --> 00:35:42,206
-I'm here to ask about Uno--
-No need for pretenses.

527
00:35:44,775 --> 00:35:48,312
"Logic doesn't solve anything."

528
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:50,214
Right?

529
00:35:56,053 --> 00:35:58,556
The year was 1995.

530
00:35:59,257 --> 00:36:01,559
April 26th.

531
00:36:03,794 --> 00:36:05,796
The burden was far too heavy

532
00:36:06,564 --> 00:36:09,467
for a seven-year-old boy to carry.

533
00:36:13,137 --> 00:36:16,240
You've walked a long way to get here.

534
00:36:19,677 --> 00:36:24,382
Could you tell me about that journey?

535
00:36:27,752 --> 00:36:31,189
Here, you don't have to hide anything.

536
00:36:35,193 --> 00:36:36,460
What happened after?

537
00:36:42,066 --> 00:36:43,534
After the incident,

538
00:36:45,336 --> 00:36:47,872
I went to live at a relative's house.

539
00:36:50,374 --> 00:36:51,475
There,

540
00:36:53,477 --> 00:36:56,247
I just waited and waited
for the culprit to be caught.

541
00:36:59,584 --> 00:37:01,586
"He'll be caught soon."

542
00:37:03,588 --> 00:37:05,823
Everyone was saying nice things like that.

543
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:07,892
But…

544
00:37:08,726 --> 00:37:12,663
as a child, you had no choice
but to believe them.

545
00:37:16,167 --> 00:37:17,435
I hoped,

546
00:37:19,403 --> 00:37:20,905
and I was let down.

547
00:37:23,608 --> 00:37:26,077
My younger brother became
more and more withdrawn.

548
00:37:29,947 --> 00:37:32,650
The police, who used to come every day,

549
00:37:34,051 --> 00:37:35,953
started coming once a week,

550
00:37:37,054 --> 00:37:38,756
then once a month.

551
00:37:40,324 --> 00:37:41,926
"We're still investigating."

552
00:37:44,428 --> 00:37:47,598
No matter how often I asked,
they only gave me the same lines.

553
00:37:52,436 --> 00:37:53,604
And then…

554
00:37:54,338 --> 00:37:56,374
the world went back to its daily routine.

555
00:38:00,811 --> 00:38:04,315
Everyone began to forget
about the incident.

556
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:13,391
Everyone…

557
00:38:15,426 --> 00:38:18,062
began to forget about the incident.

558
00:38:19,397 --> 00:38:20,331
Right.

559
00:38:21,565 --> 00:38:22,600
Everyone.

560
00:38:26,771 --> 00:38:28,139
Everyone…

561
00:38:32,877 --> 00:38:34,111
started to forget…

562
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:38,616
about my mom…

563
00:38:40,284 --> 00:38:41,419
and dad.

564
00:38:42,553 --> 00:38:46,490
As if nothing ever happened.

565
00:38:51,595 --> 00:38:52,797
I was…

566
00:38:55,299 --> 00:38:56,467
scared of that.

567
00:39:01,372 --> 00:39:02,540
And then…

568
00:39:03,174 --> 00:39:06,744
on April 26, 2010…

569
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:12,416
the case reached
its statute of limitations.

570
00:39:15,453 --> 00:39:17,388
It's only a two-day difference.

571
00:39:19,690 --> 00:39:21,392
Sometimes I think about it.

572
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:24,261
What if…

573
00:39:26,831 --> 00:39:30,034
the culprit had come just two days later?

574
00:39:32,203 --> 00:39:33,537
What if…

575
00:39:35,306 --> 00:39:38,476
the statute of limitations had been
abolished two days earlier?

576
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:42,680
We could have arrested him.

577
00:39:46,083 --> 00:39:48,185
What difference do two days make?

578
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:50,721
People were killed,

579
00:39:52,423 --> 00:39:54,258
just the same.

580
00:39:57,428 --> 00:40:00,998
The culprit doesn't just hurt you once.

581
00:40:02,633 --> 00:40:07,438
They continue to make you suffer
over and over, forever.

582
00:40:12,977 --> 00:40:16,113
Without the incident, by now,
what would you be doing?

583
00:40:20,351 --> 00:40:21,519
Gotten married?

584
00:40:24,622 --> 00:40:28,125
Or would you have gone abroad?

585
00:40:38,836 --> 00:40:40,171
To be honest…

586
00:40:41,172 --> 00:40:42,139
Yes?

587
00:40:46,043 --> 00:40:47,778
To be honest…

588
00:40:52,550 --> 00:40:54,885
I wanted a job where I could make things.

589
00:40:56,954 --> 00:40:58,322
Like my dad.

590
00:41:03,961 --> 00:41:08,632
You have been trapped in that day forever.

591
00:41:12,169 --> 00:41:14,905
How do you think it can be resolved?

592
00:41:18,442 --> 00:41:19,276
That's…

593
00:41:19,977 --> 00:41:21,512
I told you, didn't I?

594
00:41:23,180 --> 00:41:25,082
We don't need logic here.

595
00:41:29,620 --> 00:41:33,591
Even if the culprit is caught,
what changes?

596
00:41:36,494 --> 00:41:37,795
The investigation ends,

597
00:41:38,395 --> 00:41:39,897
the trial ends,

598
00:41:40,798 --> 00:41:44,468
and eventually, the culprit's punishment
comes to an end too.

599
00:41:48,806 --> 00:41:49,740
But…

600
00:41:50,841 --> 00:41:54,278
the pain of the bereaved never changes.

601
00:41:57,615 --> 00:42:00,150
Only the bereaved
who have lost their loved ones…

602
00:42:00,985 --> 00:42:02,052
Why?

603
00:42:03,454 --> 00:42:06,023
Why must they be the ones
to continue suffering?

604
00:42:11,795 --> 00:42:12,997
Makoto!

605
00:42:13,063 --> 00:42:14,698
Wait for me!

606
00:42:19,270 --> 00:42:20,304
Dad!

607
00:42:20,371 --> 00:42:21,805
Mom!

608
00:42:22,373 --> 00:42:24,975
I'll definitely find the killer!

609
00:42:38,355 --> 00:42:42,092
THINGS HAVE TURNED FOR THE WORSE

610
00:42:50,200 --> 00:42:51,335
Uno left this behind!

611
00:42:51,936 --> 00:42:54,138
Search Uno's house and its surroundings!

612
00:42:54,705 --> 00:42:56,273
The pain the victim felt,

613
00:42:57,675 --> 00:42:59,577
and the pain the perpetrator feels…

614
00:43:00,744 --> 00:43:01,912
Now, they're equal.

615
00:43:05,749 --> 00:43:07,051
They're even.

616
00:43:10,554 --> 00:43:12,289
If the culprit hasn't been caught,

617
00:43:13,724 --> 00:43:15,926
the bereaved shouldn't be arrested either.

618
00:43:18,162 --> 00:43:19,430
Nice and even.

619
00:43:22,066 --> 00:43:23,367
Nice and even.

620
00:43:28,472 --> 00:43:29,740
Nice and even.

621
00:43:48,892 --> 00:43:51,929
<i>-However you look at it, it’s suicide.</i>
-This isn't suicide, it’s murder.

622
00:43:51,996 --> 00:43:53,831
<i>She might have been inciting the murders.</i>

623
00:43:53,897 --> 00:43:55,966
Tell me what's at your core.

624
00:43:56,033 --> 00:43:57,835
Sayoko Hatano is the enemy.

625
00:43:57,901 --> 00:43:58,836
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

626
00:43:58,902 --> 00:44:00,170
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.
